    "notes": "Age: Bond 2017 §6.2 reports total age ~1.8 Gyr (cooling age 122 Myr + IFMR-derived progenitor lifetime 1.7 Gyr via Salaris+2009) with no formal sigma; the uncertainty_gyr=0.5 above is a curator estimate, not paper-stated. Spectral type DA2.9 from Gianninas, Bergeron & Ruiz 2011 (2011ApJ...743..138G, hereafter GBR11). Magnetic field: Landstreet & Bagnulo 2015 (2015A&A...580A.120L, DOI 10.1051/0004-6361/201526434) is the authoritative non-detection — high-sensitivity ESPaDOnS broad-band circular polarimetry sets an upper limit of ~250 G on any field, with mean noise sigma<Bz> ~ 85 G. Fabrika et al. 2003 (astro-ph/0006050, BSAO 55 publication) had earlier reported tentative variability with semi-amplitude ~4-5 kG and two candidate rotation periods (2h 25m, 5h 17m), but explicitly noted they could not 'determine firmly a real sole period'; the more sensitive Landstreet & Bagnulo 2015 measurement effectively refutes the kG-level detection, so no rotation entry is curated. Metallicity: Bond 2017 does not measure atmospheric [M/H]; Fabrika 2003 reports ultra-weak metal absorption lines but attributes them to circumstellar/interstellar gas (accretion from ISM and from dM4e companion 40 Eri C at ~10^-19 Msun/yr), not photospheric pollution. No DAZ-style atmospheric abundance analysis available. Activity (chromospheric): N/A for radiative-atmosphere DA WD — no convective envelope to host the Halpha/Ca II / log R'HK indicators meaningful for M and FGK dwarfs."
